{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#13544: It's possible to provide props to a slot, but no way to provide slots to slots",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:16:16.151033+00:00",
  "text": "It's possible to provide props to a slot, but no way to provide slots to slots\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.5.17\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nIn the repro link, the output is `(Default Q content from U) `\n\n\n\n### What is expected?\n\nThe expected output is `Q content from C`\n\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nInstead of providing content to `template #P`'s `<slot name=\"Q\">` from `C.vue`, the `Q content from C` is actually being ignored.\n\nPerhaps because it's treated as \"default content\" for `<slot name=\"P\">` instead of as \"invoking\" `P`\n\nIs there no way to provide content to slots within `P`?\n\n### System Info\n\n```shell\n\n```\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
